    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-03-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-03-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="150" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d150">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Burnley</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-03-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 6, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Credible information having been received
                            at this department that Vernon Gr. Locke, charged with the commission of
                            the crimes of piracy and murder on board of the United States merchant
                            steamer Chesapeake, is now a fugitive from the justice of the United
                            States at Nassau, where he is at present held under arrest, I have the
                            honor to request, through you, sir, that, conformably with the
                            provisions of the tenth article of the treaty of Washington, her
                            Britannic Majesty’s government will be pleased to issue the necessary
                            warrant for the delivery of the aforenamed Vernon <hi rend="italic">G.</hi> Locke to any person or persons duly authorized to receive
                            him, in order that he may be brought back to the United States for
                            trial.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with the highest consideration, sir, your
                            obedient</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>J. <hi rend="smallcaps">Hume Burnley,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
